view.name: Cyclist Crashes
view.description:
On Road Cyclist Crashes, since 2012, which have been reported by the Police or the Public through the AFP Crash Report Form.

Please note;
Although crash data is updated on regular bases it will always have a backlog of entries hence it is not a true reflection of the up to date crash locations.  
Crash locations are only indicative and may not reflect an accurate position of persons involved in an incident.
Casualty crashes are occasionally omitted from some maps or crash reports if they are still under investigation.

columns.name: CRASH_ID
columns.description: A unique identifier of a crash record, compiled from possibly multiple crash reports received for the crash.

columns.name: CRASH_DATE
columns.description: The date of the crash.  This is stored as both the date and time.

columns.name: SEVERITY
columns.description: This is a summarised severity of the crash.  If there has been a fatality, the severity will be Fatal.  If any injuries have been incurred, the severitiy will be Injury.  All other crashes are Property Damage.

columns.name: CRASH_TYPE
columns.description: This is the description of the type of crash, including details on direction, section of car, objects involved in the collision and position on road.

columns.name: CYCLISTS
columns.description: The number of reported cyclists involved in the crash.

columns.name: CYCLIST_CASUALTIES
columns.description: The number of reported cyclists injured in the crash.

columns.name: REPORTED_LOCATION
columns.description: The location, either a section of road or intersection, as interpreted from the crash reports received for the crash.

columns.name: LATITUDE
columns.description: The Latitude in WGS84 format for the generalised location of the crash, positioned on the road network centreline, as interpreted from the crash reports received for the crash.

columns.name: LONGITUDE
columns.description: The Longitude in WGS84 format for the generalised location of the crash, positioned on the road network centreline, as interpreted from the crash reports received for the crash.

columns.name: LOCATION_1
columns.description: The combination of the LATITUDE and LONGITUDE fields.
